reviews.text: Went in early at 11:45AM, food took a while to arrive, waiter messed up my order of milk tea, AC constantly dripping water, address to waiter but was ignored. Order the curry Laksa, came in with a big bowl of noodles, four tiny fish balls and one shrimp, sets you almost hkd80 back. My friends didn't finish their pad Thais, to be fair, pad Thais weren't bad, just a little salty and chicken a little tasteless. Green curry chicken rice tastes good, but watery. Next to us, a table of six tried to explain their orders of iced teas, some with less sugar, some with no ice, poor waiter, who's probably too new couldn't manage. Overall the restaurant is too new, nice decor, very mediocre food (poor for the price), inexperienced kitchen and restaurant management. Sorry to leave a bad review, but hopefully it will improve over time. Good luck.
